06/07/2003
MOSCOW, Russia -- The presidents of Romania and Russia signed a friendship agreement Friday (4 July), signaling the warming of relations after 13 years of strain. 
Vladimir Putin and Ion Iliescu agreed to develop closer ties in the energy, transportation, raw materials, engineering, agriculture and food sectors. 
The agreement provides for better use of the resources of the Black Sea and co-operation in transportation on the Danube. 
On Saturday, Iliescu inaugurated the country's new general consulate in St Petersburg. 
(Rompres, Mediafax - 05/07/03; AFP - 04/07/03)
